This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) because it proposes a novel Quality Estimation model for summarization based on BERT, which is a popular language model used in NLP. Additionally, the paper addresses linguistic quality aspects that are only indirectly captured by content-based approaches to summary evaluation, which is a common problem in NLP. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. 

Furthermore, the paper deals with information retrieval and text generation, which are relevant to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper proposes a model that can be used for system development, which is relevant to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
